[4. MEXICAN CUSTOMS (ADUANA) & LEGAL PROTOCOLS]
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Golden Rule: Keep EVERY retail receipt organized in a folder. 
* Tax Calculation: Mexican Customs calculates your 16% import tax based on your 
  receipt totals. If you lose receipts, they tax you on FULL retail value ($300+ 
  per bucket), destroying your profit margin.
* Crossing Procedure (Tijuana / Otay Mesa):
    1. Stay LEFT and enter the "Autodeclaración / Voluntary Declaration" Lane.
    2. Never go to the "Nothing to Declare" green-light lane with commercial cargo.
    3. Hand the agent the receipt folder, state you have surplus household paint.
    4. Pay the tax fee ($32 for Test Trip / $80 for Full Trip) via cash or card.
    5. Keep the official paper receipt safely in the glove compartment.

[5. HIGHWAY 1 DRIVING & DISTRIBUTION LOGISTICS]
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Packing Safety: 
    - Lay a heavy tarp over the entire floor area.
    - Pack buckets tightly together so they cannot shift or tip during cornering.
    - In the Tercel, place buckets on the floor behind front seats, NOT the trunk.
* The Baja Route (Federal Highway 1):
    - Tijuana to Guerrero Negro is a ~9 to 10 hour grueling drive. 
    - San Quintín is your last major city. Fill up your gas tank completely here.
    - Cataviña Desert Alert: There is a notorious 150-mile gap with no official 
      gas stations. Keep a spare 5-gallon fuel jug in your vehicle.
* Military Checkpoints: You will pass multiple Sedena (Military) checkpoints. 
  When they search the vehicle and see bulk paint, show them your official 
  Aduana import tax receipt. They will let you pass without issue.
* Sales Execution:
    - Change Facebook Marketplace location to Guerrero Negro / Bahía de los Ángeles 
      48 hours before arrival. Post photos of bucket lids showing the color sample.
    - Visit local construction sites and "Ferreterías" (hardware stores) directly 
      to move bulk inventory instantly to cash-ready contractors.
